---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../../styles/globals.css";
import { Header } from "../../components/Header";
import InnerPageCTA from "../../components/InnerPageCTA.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";

const b = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout
  title="How US Retailers Can Exceed Expectations on Sustainability - parcelLab"
  description="Learn why sustainability matters more than ever to US consumers and how retailers can improve packaging, shipping, supply chains, and transparency."
>
  <Header client:load />
  <main>
    <!-- Article Header -->
    <section class="section-generous">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1440px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px]">
          <a href={`${b}/blog/`} class="group mb-8 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--ink-muted)] transition-colors hover:text-[#3D3AD3]">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="transition-transform group-hover:-translate-x-0.5"><path d="M19 12H5"/><path d="m12 19-7-7 7-7"/></svg>
            Back to blog
          </a>
          <span class="mb-4 inline-block rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-[#3D3AD3]">Shipping</span>
          <h1 class="text-display text-[var(--ink)]">How US Retailers Can Exceed Expectations on Sustainability</h1>
          <div class="mt-6 flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-[var(--ink-muted)]">
            <span>By <strong class="font-medium text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">parcelLab Team</strong></span>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <time datetime="2022-06-11">June 11, 2022</time>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <span>6 min read</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Article Body -->
    <section class="pb-16 md:pb-24">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed text-lg">
          Are your products sustainable? What about your shipping carrier? And most importantly -- do your customers see your business as sustainable? Sustainability has become a key factor in how US consumers make decisions. And e-commerce retailers are just starting to catch up.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">Customers Care About Sustainability</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          For a long time, both customers and retailers thought of sustainability as a "nice to have." That has changed. Consumers now actively look for sustainable products, services, and post-purchase experiences.
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">Millennials and Gen Z are <strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">25% more likely</strong> to check sustainability ratings before buying</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]"><strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">48% of US consumers</strong> say they've become more concerned about sustainability in the last 2 years</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]"><strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">72% of shoppers</strong> are actively buying more sustainable products than 5 years ago</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]"><strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">64% of Americans</strong> are willing to pay more for sustainable products</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">How Retailers Can Improve E-Commerce Sustainability</h2>

        <div class="mt-6 space-y-6">
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">Sustainable Packaging</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              E-commerce retailers now have access to recycled materials, recyclable or compostable options, and lightweight packaging innovations that reduce waste without compromising product protection.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">Sustainable Shipping</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              Consumer research shows demand for shipping carrier choices, including sustainable services. Currently, only 6% of US businesses use carbon-neutral delivery, and just 4% offer reduced packaging options -- positioning early adopters ahead of competitors.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">Sustainable Supply Chains</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              Knowledge enables positive change. Understanding product sourcing allows retailers to make informed improvements. This is why proposed New York legislation mandates minimum data transparency about supply chains.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">Transparency</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              Consumers willingly pay more for sustainable options -- retailers must actively communicate these efforts throughout the buyer journey and post-purchase experience to showcase their environmental credentials.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="my-12 border-t border-[var(--line)]"></div>

        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          Repeated surveys reveal consumers want sustainable options but feel uncertain about what sustainability actually means. The most successful e-commerce retailers educate and inform customers about their green initiatives, turning sustainability into a competitive advantage.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <InnerPageCTA />
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
